Budget Buddy
Project Goals
Budget Buddy is a simple and intuitive budgeting application built with .NET MAUI to help users manage their personal finances. The app enables users to track their transactions, view their current balance, and store data persistently using SQLite. The primary goal of Budget Buddy is to provide an easy-to-use tool for managing budgets on mobile devices, making financial tracking accessible to everyone.

Features
Add new transactions with a user-defined amount and description.

View a list of all past transactions.

Track your balance in real-time.

Persistent storage of transaction history using SQLite.

Instructions for Building and Running the Application
Prerequisites
Before building Budget Buddy, ensure you have the following installed:

.NET 8 SDK

Visual Studio 2022 (with .NET MAUI workload installed)

SQLite NuGet package

Steps to Build and Run
Clone the repository

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/budget-buddy.git
cd budget-buddy
Open the project

Launch Visual Studio 2022.

Open the .sln file for Budget Buddy.

Install NuGet packages

Go to Tools → NuGet Package Manager → Manage NuGet Packages for Solution.

Install:

sqlite-net-pcl

CommunityToolkit.Mvvm

Run the app

Select a target platform (Android, iOS, or Windows).

Press F5 to build and run the application.
